ENTRY            M0778   20260121   20260302   20260302       M144
SUBENT        M0778001   20260121   20260302   20260302       M144
BIB                 11         39
TITLE      Low-energy photon scattering experiments of 151,153Eu,
            163Dy, and 165Ho and the systematics of the M1
            scissors mode in odd-mass rare-earth nuclei.
AUTHOR     (A.Nord,J.Enders,A.E.De Almedia Pinto,D.Belic,
            P.Von Brentano,C.Fransen,U.Kneissl,C.Kohstall,
            A.Linnemann,P.Von Neumann-Cosel,N.Pietralla,
            H.H.Pitz,A.Richter,F.Stedile,V.Werner)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,67,034307,2003)
           #doi:10.1103/PhysRevC.67.034307
INSTITUTE  (2GERTHS,1USAMSU,3BZLUSP,2GERKLN,2GERTHD)
FACILITY   (LINAC,2GERTHS) Stuttgart Dynamitron accelerator.
INC-SOURCE (BRST) Bremsstrahlung with end-point energy of 4.05.
           Two measurements were carried out to achieve an
            optimal sensitivity over a broad range of excitation
            energies, and to enable the detection of weaker
            decay branching.
SAMPLE     The nuclear resonance fluorescence targets were
            sandwiched by 27Al disks serving for the photon flux
            calibration. Target compositions and specifications:
            isotope composition  enrich.   total        major
                                  (%)    masses (mg)    impur.
                                         target 27Al     (%)
            151Eu    Eu2O3       99.24    2161   781 153Eu (0.76)
            153Eu    Eu2O3       99.81    1729  1016 151Eu (0.19)
            163Dy    Dy2O3       89.9     2530   506 161Dy (0.26)
                                                     162Dy (1.82)
                                                     164Dy (8.02)
            165Ho    Ho2O3      100.      2697   763
            165Ho   Ho metal    100.      2115   781
DETECTOR   (HPGE) 3 high-resolution Ge-detectors with energy
            resolution about 2 keV at a photon energy of 1.3 MeV
            and about 3 keV at 3 MeV installed at angles of
            about 90, 127 and 150 degree.
METHOD     (GSPEC)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information.
HISTORY    (20090618C) Russia MSU SINP CDFE by V.Varlamov.
           (20111117A) Corrected by V.Varlamov: AUTHOR, doi.
           (20260121A) Corrected by VV and SD: TITLE, DATA,
            STATUS.
ENDBIB              39
